Title: A relativistically covariant stochastic model for systems with a
  fluctuating number of particles
Authors: L. M. Morato and L. Viola
Comments: 5 Pages; no figures; Plain REVTeX style. To be published in Phys.
  Lett. A
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. A246 (1998) 214-218
\\
  We construct a relativistically covariant stochastic model for systems of
non-interacting spinless particles whose number undergoes random fluctuations.
The model is compared with the canonical quantization of the free scalar field
in the limit of infinite volume.
